message.content: Based on the provided volatility data, a possible payload of the initial exploit affecting the victim's bank account could be the file "sdra64.exe" located in \Device\HarddiskVolume1\WINDOWS\system32\. This file appears to be related to the suspicious activity and could be the Remote Access Trojan (RAT) that was hidden within the msiexec.exe process. Further analysis of the "sdra64.exe" file is recommended to confirm its malicious nature and its connection to the unusual bank account activity.
